<br>
<br>
He first came to this spot with Somma.  They would sit together, calmly and talking about the past.  They would comtemplate the way things have changed.  They would chuckle at the way things stayed the same.  Here, in this lonely desert by the ocean, Somma and Aryllyian would talk about foolish pride and their love for Elves and Tunare.  They would talk about women, good music and about good times.<br>
<br>
On one cold morning, Somma told Aryllyian that the distant glimmer on the horizon was calling him.  Calling him away from our guildhall...<br>
<br>
Aryllyian stood motionless for a long time, not knowing what to do or say.<br>
<br>
Finally...after careful thought. <br>
<br>
Aryllyian asked Somma for one more hunt.  Just one more before he left.<br>
<br>
