A small page had told her where he had gone.  She had started for the door, then remembering the heat of the desert and the long climb, had returned to her quarters to change out of her battle armor.   She put on the white Ulthork armor, lighter in weight and better suited for travelling.<br>
<br>
Now as she slogged through the sand she wondered what she would say when she found him.  A snatch of a song that Aseop sang flitted through her head:<br>
<br>
Gaily bedight,<br>
A gallant knight,<br>
In sunshine and in shadow,<br>
Had journeyed long,<br>
Singing a song,<br>
In search of Eldorado.<br>
<br>
But he grew old --<br>
This knight so bold --<br>
And o'er his heart a shadow<br>
Fell as he found<br>
No spot of ground<br>
That looked like Eldorado.<br>
<br>
There was a shadow on Ary's heart, no doubt. He was older than her in years, streaks of white in his red hair, but even though older he was somehow more vulnerable in spirit.  A tear rolled down her cheek, a tear of regret that her buffs only shielded agains blows to the body, not the spirit.  She held the soft leather skirt up to avoid stepping on it as she began to climb the hill to Land's End.<br>
<br>
At the top she found him, squinting into the sunset.  Nothing to say, she reflected.  How can I address wounds to the spirit?  Refresh an aching soul?  Wiping more tears away, she walked up to his side, and reaching up, pushed away a strand of hair that had fallen across his brow.  She smiled mistily at his beloved, familiar face.  Silently she took his hand, and turned to watch the sun's glorious spectacle.<br>
<br>
I wonder if I could get him to watch a sunrise?  she mused.  Just as beautiful, but not so melancholy.  A sunrise for hope... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#BA9F70><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/belvenelite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aryllyian>Aryllyian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer</span><br>  Posts: 1273<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(10/16/02 9:53:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=78.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aryllyian's Lament</span><hr size=1> Aryllyian searched for words and found himself unable to speak.  He swallowed hard and tried to choke down the emotion that would have cracked every word he tried to speak.  He lowered his head as he tried to avoid eye contact with Seyah.  It had always been clear to Aryllyian that the Priestess was in Tunare's fullest favor.  He could barely look upon her face and not become awash in emotion.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Simpler not to say anything,&quot; mumbled Ary under his breath while casting his eyes skyward.      <br>
